@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p class="text-muted"><em>Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.Year</em></p>

<p>
    JosephGuadagno.NET Broadcasting (<strong>"this application"</strong>) is a personal automation tool used exclusively
    by Joseph Guadagno to collect content from RSS feeds and YouTube and distribute it to social media platforms.
    It is not a public-facing consumer service.
</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<p>
    This application does <strong>not</strong> collect, store, or process any personal data from end users or site visitors.
    There are no sign-up forms, contact forms, or analytics tracking directed at visitors. The only data stored is
    content metadata (blog post titles, URLs, talk descriptions, scheduling timestamps) that belongs to Joseph Guadagno.
</p>

<h2>Authentication</h2>
<p>
    Access to this application is restricted to authorised users via Microsoft identity (Azure AD / Entra ID).
    A session cookie is set upon successful authentication to maintain your signed-in state. This cookie is
    strictly necessary for the application to function and is not used for tracking or advertising.
    It expires when your browser session ends or when you sign out.
</p>

<h2>Cookies</h2>
<p>This application uses only the following cookie:</p>
<table class="table table-bordered table-sm" style="max-width: 600px;">
    <thead class="table-light">
    <tr>
        <th>Cookie</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Duration</th>
    </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    <tr>
        <td><code>.AspNetCore.Cookies</code></td>
        <td>Authentication session — keeps you signed in</td>
        <td>Session / sign-out</td>
    </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<p>No third-party tracking, advertising, or analytics cookies are used.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>
    This application integrates with the following external platforms to publish content on behalf of the owner.
    Your use of those platforms is governed by their own privacy policies:
</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="https://twitter.com/en/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitter / X Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/policy.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Facebook / Meta Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://bsky.social/about/support/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bluesky Privacy Policy</a></li>
</ul>
<p>
    API credentials for these services are stored securely in Azure Key Vault and are never exposed to end users
    or committed to source control.
</p>

<h2>Data Retention</h2>
<p>
    Engagement, talk, and schedule data is retained in the application database for as long as needed
    by the owner and is deleted on demand. No personal data belonging to third parties is stored.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>
    If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact:
    <a href="mailto:joseph@josephguadagno.net">joseph@josephguadagno.net</a>
</p>